    reasoning: Signature is `Result<NaplMap, _>`. Prompt distinguishes two failure modes ("unsupported map version" validation error vs. corrupt-JSON deserialization error) but never names the error type unifying them. Existing code already picked one (no change needed here), but the prompt itself does not pin the type — a re-implementer would have to guess (e.g. a custom enum, Box<dyn Error>, serde_json::Error, String).
